# Project Rules

## Project Identity

This project is a reusable Arabic-first Restaurant CMS Platform. The first implementation is for a seafood restaurant.

## Language And Routing

- Arabic is the default and primary language.
- The public website opens in Arabic by default.
- Default public route is `/ar`.
- English public route is `/en`.
- Arabic pages use RTL.
- English pages use LTR.
- Admin dashboard is Arabic-first.
- Admin dashboard can support English later.
- Every editable public content field must support Arabic and English.

## CMS Rules

- Do not permanently hardcode restaurant text in application code.
- Restaurant content should come from database records or admin settings when possible.
- Seafood-specific content should be configurable so the platform remains reusable.
- Manager image, logo, favicon, hero images, theme, SEO, menu, offers, gallery, reviews, reservations, messages, and contact settings are owner-managed concepts.

## Seafood Menu Rules

- Default seafood categories: الأسماك الطازجة، المأكولات البحرية، الأطباق الخاصة، طرق الطهي، خدمات المطعم.
- Menu items support `nameAr`, `nameEn`, `descriptionAr`, and `descriptionEn`.
- Menu items can have multiple price variants.
- Variants support `nameAr`, `nameEn`, `price`, and `unit`.
- Supported units include كجم، حبة، طبق، صغير، كبير.
- Cooking methods are dynamic and editable from admin.
- Admin can hide unavailable items and mark featured items.

## Security And SEO Rules

- Admin login is required.
- Admin pages are protected.
- Use roles and permissions.
- Validate all forms.
- Reviews are not public until approved.
- Customer email and phone data must never appear publicly.
- Arabic SEO is primary; English SEO is supported.
- Support `sitemap.xml`, `robots.txt`, JSON-LD structured data, and Open Graph.

## Implementation Discipline

- Do not modify application code during documentation-only tasks.
- Do not modify the `app` folder unless the user explicitly requests implementation.
- Do not install packages or modify `package.json` unless explicitly requested.
- Before writing Next.js application code, read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
